    "details": {
      "blurb": "Night hag soul-trader (B19)",
      "languages": {
        "details": "",
        "value": [
          "abyssal",
          "common",
          "infernal",
          "orcish"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 10
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role (B19, social encounter):</strong> a night hag newly arrived to trade souls with Mithrodar (who shields her from the curse), nested in the old apothecary among netting-bags and a Styx-weed brazier. The B18 @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-hazards.Actor.polongBottles001]{polong-bottle trap} is her rigging — the bottled murderers a gift from the chained spirit. <strong>The con:</strong> hearing battle, she becomes 'Alimae' and tries to lead the PCs to C14 to <em>sell them</em> to Mithrodar in exchange for an anchor spirit. <strong>Exposed, she reverts with a cackle but still doesn't attack</strong> — she proposes alliance instead: she helps the PCs defeat a spirit anchor so she can jar its soul and flee to Abaddon. <strong>Her intel (genuine):</strong> Mithrodar cannot be destroyed while his four anchors exist; hundreds of spirits are bound in the walls; <strong>Castothrane, Belshallam, and Nihil</strong> are anchors (she knows the way to Belshallam's lair, prefers Nihil's soul) and she suspects — correctly — the fourth lies in <strong>the chapel to the north</strong>. <strong>Betrayal clause:</strong> if she learns the PCs mean to destroy Mithrodar <em>himself</em> (voiding her market), she stays allied only until an anchor-soul is caught, then warns Mithrodar, seeking a second soul as payment — <em>he kills her for it</em>, and the PCs find her body in C14, her own spirit tormented in his chains. <strong>Morale:</strong> flees below ~75 HP to her nightmare steed (C9), rides out the C15 parapet, and goes ethereal once outside — possibly returning to dream-haunt the party in Chapter 6.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
        "authors": "",
        "license": "OGL",
        "remaster": true
      }
